trade unions say their members are having to pay for an economic crisis that has been created by corrupt politicians .
the vice president of the civil servants' union , elias vrettakos , told sky news : "the measures of the government overtake our historic gains and abolish our rights and return society back to the 1960s . " .
other union leaders have called the cuts "savage attacks on workers' rights" .
